<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'>We can observe how the NMF and MLP model
consistently outperform the MF model, while higher negative samples can res=
ult
in that performance gap becoming smaller. We can conclude that the MF model
relies much more strongly on the existence of negative samples for classifi=
cation,
than the MLP and NMF models. Infact, if we consider a case where we increase
the number of negative samples a lot, the MF Model will likely perform than=
 the
MLP model. The same isn’t very apparent for the accuracy metrics of the MF
model…<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'>We can see a drop in the performance of the=
 MLP
and NeuMF models in the last 2 rows. This is an indication of overfitting –=
 the
models have turned to memorising the training data, and thus have performed
more poorly in the testing data. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'>The NeuMF model performs better than the fi=
rst
two in almost all cases, because it is able to keep track of linear trends =
using
the MF model, and account for non-linearities at low no. of negative samples
using the NCF/MLP model. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'>Increasing the embed dimension will result =
in
higher scores for all the models, as it results in more “accurate” embedding
vectors with respect to the original dataset.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:9.0pt;line-height:107%;font-f=
amily:
"Bahnschrift Light",sans-serif'>I would like to end of my report with an ap=
ology
for submitting all of this 2-days past the deadline…<o:p></o:p></span></p>

